> This obviously doesn't work for Docker APIv2. My proposal was force Docker APIv2 to only use `docker.io` but @vrothberg had objections to that.

I am more supportive of this idea now.  The only remark I have is that the project-atomic docker did use search registries for pulling but since that can be a security issue, I am feel more inclined to just enforce docker.io.

@mtrmac what do you think?

@vrothberg speaking of ignition files: I noticed that in VM `core`'s user home is `/var/home/core` not `/home/core`. But IIUIC  ignition assumes `/home/core` https://github.com/containers/podman/blob/main/pkg/machine/ignition.go#L156
EDIT: are those somehow linked?
EDIT2: I see now those are symlinks.
